"description": "#### Which Events API version should I use?

##### Version 2 (Recommended)
Enables advanced event and incident management functionality from any system that can make HTTP API calls.
Directly send structured monitoring data to PagerDuty and use it to visualize and manage your events and alerts thanks to [PagerDuty’s Common Event Format](https://support.pagerduty.com/docs/pd-cef).

[Learn more about Events API v2 and view documentation](https://v2.developer.pagerduty.com/docs/events-api-v2)

##### Version 1
Enables basic event and incident management from any system that can make HTTP API calls to PagerDuty. Use this with custom monitoring tools that do not yet support API v2
column2:
or if you need to apply [event transforms](https://v2.developer.pagerduty.com/docs/cet) to your data.

[View documentation for Events API v1](https://v2.developer.pagerduty.com/docs/events-api)
